verses.roman:
ananta guṇa śrī-rādhikāra, pañciśa--pradhāna
yei guṇera 'vaśa' haya kṛṣṇa bhagavān

synonyms: ananta guṇa—unlimited qualities; śrī-rādhikāra—of Śrīmatī Rādhārāṇī; pañciśa—twenty-five; pradhāna—chief; yei guṇera—of those qualities; vaśa—under the control; haya—is; kṛṣṇa—Lord Kṛṣṇa; bhagavān—the Supreme Personality of Godhead.
translation: "Similarly, Śrīmatī Rādhārāṇī has unlimited transcendental qualities, of which twenty-five qualities are principal. Śrī Kṛṣṇa is controlled by these transcendental qualities of Śrīmatī Rādhārāṇī.
